# Food Delivery App - Design System

This document outlines the basic visual design guidelines for the Food Delivery App to ensure consistency across the user interface.

## 1. Colors

* **Primary:** `#FF5C01` (Vibrant Orange - for buttons, highlights, key actions)
* **Secondary:** `#4CAF50` (Green - for success states, confirmation, delivery indicators)
* **Accent:** `#FFC107` (Amber - for ratings, special offers)
* **Background:**
    * `#FFFFFF` (White - primary background)
    * `#F5F5F5` (Light Gray - for cards, sections, subtle divisions)
* **Text:**
    * `#212121` (Near Black - primary text)
    * `#757575` (Medium Gray - secondary text, subtitles, placeholders)
    * `#FFFFFF` (White - text on dark/colored backgrounds)
* **Status/Feedback:**
    * **Error:** `#D32F2F` (Red)
    * **Warning:** `#FFA000` (Orange/Yellow)
    * **Success:** `#388E3C` (Darker Green)
    * **Info:** `#1976D2` (Blue)

## 2. Typography

* **Font Family:** `Inter` (Use `google_fonts` package to import)
    * Ensure weights `Regular (400)`, `Medium (500)`, `SemiBold (600)`, `Bold (700)` are available.
* **Font Sizes & Styles:**
    * **Headline Large (H1):** 32sp, Bold (700) - *Use sparingly, e.g., onboarding*
    * **Headline Medium (H2):** 24sp, Bold (700) - *Screen titles*
    * **Headline Small (H3):** 20sp, SemiBold (600) - *Section titles, important labels*
    * **Title Large:** 18sp, Medium (500) - *Card titles, list item primary text*
    * **Title Medium:** 16sp, Medium (500) - *Dialog titles, button text*
    * **Body Large:** 16sp, Regular (400) - *Main content text*
    * **Body Medium:** 14sp, Regular (400) - *Secondary text, descriptions, input field text*
    * **Label Large:** 14sp, Medium (500) - *Form labels, captions*
    * **Label Medium:** 12sp, Regular (400) - *Helper text, timestamps, small captions*
    * **Label Small:** 10sp, Regular (400) - *Very small text, tags*
* **Line Height:** Generally 1.4x - 1.5x the font size for body text for readability.

## 3. Layout & Spacing

* **Base Unit:** 8dp (Use multiples of this for consistent spacing)
* **Common Spacing Values:**
    * `xxs`: 4dp
    * `xs`: 8dp
    * `s`: 12dp
    * `m`: 16dp (Standard padding around elements/screens)
    * `l`: 24dp
    * `xl`: 32dp
    * `xxl`: 48dp
* **Screen Padding:** Default horizontal padding of `16dp` (`m`) on most screens.
* **List Item Spacing:** Use `8dp` (`xs`) or `12dp` (`s`) vertical spacing between items in lists.
* **Grid:** Use standard Column/Row layouts. For card grids, ensure consistent spacing (`m`).
* **Max Content Width:** For very wide screens (tablets), consider constraining the main content width to enhance readability (e.g., max 800dp).

## 4. Components

* **Buttons:**
    * **Primary:** Solid background (Primary color), White text, rounded corners (8dp), standard padding (e.g., `12dp` vertical, `24dp` horizontal).
    * **Secondary:** Outlined (Primary color border), Primary color text, rounded corners (8dp), standard padding.
    * **Text:** No background/border, Primary color text.
    * **Disabled State:** Reduced opacity (e.g., 50%), non-interactive.
* **Cards:**
    * Background: Light Gray (`#F5F5F5`) or White (`#FFFFFF`).
    * Corner Radius: 8dp or 12dp.
    * Elevation/Shadow: Subtle shadow to lift off the background.
    * Padding: Internal padding of `16dp` (`m`).
* **Input Fields:**
    * Outlined style preferred.
    * Rounded corners (4dp or 8dp).
    * Clear label (Label Large/Medium).
    * Placeholder text (Body Medium, Medium Gray).
    * Helper/Error text below (Label Medium).
* **Navigation Bar (Bottom):** Standard platform component. Use clear icons and labels (Label Medium). Active state highlighted with Primary color.
* **App Bar:** Standard app bar. Title (Headline Small/Medium), optional back button, action icons (e.g., Cart).
* **Images:** Use `aspectRatio` and ` BoxFit.cover` for consistency. Rounded corners (match card radius if inside a card). Use placeholders while loading (`CachedNetworkImage`).

## 5. Iconography

* **Source:** Material Icons (built into Flutter) or a consistent custom set.
* **Style:** Filled or Outlined (choose one style for consistency).
* **Size:** Standard sizes (e.g., 18dp, 24dp). Ensure icons are clear and easily understandable.
* **Color:** Use Text colors (Primary/Secondary) or specific icon tints where appropriate.

## 6. Accessibility

* Ensure sufficient color contrast (use contrast checkers).
* Provide semantic labels for interactive elements (buttons, icons) for screen readers.
* Support dynamic font scaling where possible.
* Ensure adequate touch target sizes (minimum 44x44dp).